<br>
1) You gave around 24 hours warning.  Even most of the people active in KCoG do not check this board every day.  1 Day warning is simply not enough time for the word to get out.<br>
<br>
2) Your loot rules, while they are reasonable with your guild hosting the event, do not leave a lot of incentive for people outside your guild to come, particularly anyone who wants a jade reaver or would come to primarily support one of their friends to get a Jade Reaver.  When you setup loot rules like this, then chances are that you will not get a lot of participation, especially in a place like CoM where many guilds rot while trying to equip all of their druids and rangers with those jade reavers.  <br>
<br>
3) Many people are sick of CoM, because of the Jade Reavers.  I know my guild has several people that refuse to step inside CoM because of the amount of time they have spent killing black reavers for friends and guildmates.<br>
<br>
I am not saying that you shouldn't expect anyone to show up to an event like this, but factor in all three things and you can see why no one did.  More warning, and the ability to have a chance at those jade reavers and whatnot else would much increase the chance that people would come. <p>Farrnusno <BR>
Guild Leader of Souls of the Valiant <BR>
